(harness can hide real regressions in future runs because it fails too early for wrong reasons.) Tj
T*
(Recommended fix is to update the harness templates to current constants and block-shape) Tj
T*
(requirements so strict suites measure intended predicates.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q5\) How is public double spend blocked?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Three layers:) Tj
T*
(- Transaction-level duplicate outpoint rejection.) Tj
T*
(- Mempool reservation/index conflict rejection for already-referenced outpoints.) Tj
T*
(- UTXO store spent-status checks at admission and verifier paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Together these prevent both same-tx and cross-tx mempool spend collisions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q6\) How is private double spend blocked?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Private spends use nullifiers plus commit tracking:) Tj
T*
(- Nullifier must be unique per spend.) Tj
T*
(- Nullifier cannot already be confirmed.) Tj
T*
(- Nullifier cannot be pending in another tx.) Tj
T*
(- Input commit cannot be duplicated in same tx.) Tj
T*
(- Input commit collision can be detected in block overlay and mempool index.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is the private equivalent of UTXO spend reservation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q7\) Can an attacker fake a private note and spend it?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Not if the validator path is followed:) Tj
T*
(- Commit must exist in private note store.) Tj
T*
(- note_pk in tx input must match stored note.) Tj
T*
(- Anchor must be valid at the reference height.) Tj
T*
(- Merkle path must verify.) Tj
T*
(- Spend signature must verify against the stored note public key and computed digest.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Without all of those, spend is rejected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q8\) Can someone reuse a nullifier but make it look different?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The nullifier is normalized and tracked. Reuse across casing/format variants is handled because) Tj
T*
(values are parsed and normalized before checks. Duplicate or pending/confirmed collisions are) Tj
T*
(rejected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q9\) Can someone include two private spends of same note in one block?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The new overlay checks reduce this risk significantly:) Tj
T*
(- Per-block private input commit overlay now rejects same-commit double spend in a block) Tj
T*
(assembly cycle.) Tj
T*
(- Nullifier overlays also block repeated nullifier references.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q10\) Can someone create money from thin air with private amounts hidden?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In normal validated flows, no. The system uses private amount commitments and block-level) Tj
T*
(proof/accumulator gates. However, this is a sensitive area: correctness depends on enforcement) Tj
T*
