(Q11\) Is private tx malleability still possible?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key defenses:) Tj
T*
(- Private spend preimage uses txid_without_signatures and normalized payload rules.) Tj
T*
(- Private input signatures are verified on deterministic digest construction.) Tj
T*
(- Deterministic v5 block conversion for amount_commit removes conversion drift.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Residual risk is lower now than before deterministic conversion patch.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q12\) Why was deterministic v5 conversion necessary?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If mempool-form private outputs and block-form private outputs use non-deterministic conversion) Tj
T*
(inputs, signatures and expected commitments can desync across contexts, causing valid-looking tx) Tj
T*
(to fail at block time. Deterministic conversion makes conversion reproducible and removes that) Tj
T*
(attack/failure surface.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q13\) How does the system stop output commitment duplication?) Tj
T*
(- In-tx duplicate output commit rejection.) Tj
T*
(- Mempool output-commit index conflict checks.) Tj
T*
(- Existing confirmed note commit collision checks.) Tj
T*
(- Block overlay checks for duplicate output commits.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q14\) Can a tx with malformed private fields bypass checks?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Parsing enforces field shape and constraints first. Invalid encoding or missing required fields) Tj
T*
(causes parse failure before spend logic. This is a fail-closed design point.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q15\) Does private tx require top-level pubkey/signature?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For pure private-input spends, authentication is done by per-input private signatures bound to) Tj
T*
(note ownership and spend digest. Public-input transactions still require top-level) Tj
T*
(witness/signature handling.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q16\) What about replay attacks on old private spends?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Replay of a spent private note should fail due to nullifier confirmed/pending checks and note) Tj
T*
(spent status. Replay of public spends fails via UTXO spent-status and mempool reservation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
