(Q19\) How are fee-based mempool replacement attacks handled?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Mempool replacement policy enforces fee delta and fee-rate bump requirements. Low-quality) Tj
T*
(replacement attempts should fail and not evict better pending tx.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q20\) Is dust spam blocked?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Public outputs are dust-checked against configured dust limit. Outputs below threshold are) Tj
T*
(rejected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q21\) Is coinbase maturity enforced?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Yes. Spends of coinbase UTXO are blocked until required confirmation threshold is reached.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q22\) Are lockup roles \(bond/stake\) protected?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Yes, role-based spend constraints are enforced. The signer must match the role-derived owner) Tj
T*
(address, and lockup spend operations require appropriate metadata and unlockable state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q23\) Can attacker bypass ownership by setting tx_input.address?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
